cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a machine learning model for predicting road surface friction using historical data. Specifically, it uses a Gated Recurrent Unit network-based decay mechanism to handle missing values in the data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for predicting road surface conditions. It also discusses the impact of missing data on the accuracy and efficiency of the model, which falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of recurrent neural networks for time-series prediction suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
